Rainy conditions are expected to continue over most parts of KwaZulu-Natal on Wednesday. Heavy rains fell across most areas Tuesday night. South African Weather Services forecaster, Wisani Maluleke says there’s an 80% chance of showers throughout the day in the coastal areas, while in the rest of the province, there’s a 60% chance. He says the conditions are expected to start clearing Thursday afternoon. He says: “We are expecting a bit of cold temperatures in the northern parts of the province. Then on Thursday the areas where we expecting rain its only the north eastern parts of the province that includes Durban, Richards Bay and Ulundi. It will still remain cloudy and then becoming partly towards the afternoon.” 